cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a cyber-physical testbed design and implementation for verifying and demonstrating wide-area control methods based on streaming telemetry and phasor measurement unit data. The paper also presents demonstrations of two wide-area measurement-based controls - system separation control and hierarchical voltage control. These aspects suggest that the paper belongs to the Systems and Control sub-category.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a decoupled architecture composed of a software-defined network and integrated over industry-standard communication protocols. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture sub-category.
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper mentions a scripting language environment for prototyping an EMS system and a control system. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Programming Languages sub-category.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a cyber-physical testbed design and implementation that involves multiple components and systems, which suggests that the paper belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing sub-category.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper mentions the use of open-source software packages managed by a Python dispatcher. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Software Engineering sub-category.
